If possible, consider visiting a discount floral supply or even dollar store as well because that type of establishment might have everything you need as well--at a greater discount. Pick up glass containers to hold the flowers. Look for a shape and design that will compliment your party. Something simple and timeless, but a design that enhances the overall theme. Purchase the amount you will need for the entire party (this includes whether you want multiple containers on tables). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Consider buying containers in different sizes as well. You could do a centerpiece with three different heights and widths to add interest, for example. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/46/Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/46/Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

You will need to customize the flower size to fit inside the container. Size flowers as you do each container (so don't size all of them at once). Bend stems and twist flowers so they can be placed inside the container. This is simply to see how short or how the flowers will look inside the vase. You should also get an idea of how many flowers you'll need inside each container as well. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e3/Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e3/Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Snip the stems once you are satisfied with the length and number of flowers inside the container. Also, consider whether you need to trim leaves, etc. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/44/Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/44/Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Elegant-Centerpieces-Using-Distilled-Water-and-Silk-Flowers-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
